==Chinese==

===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{liushu|ic}}: {{zh-l|*彳|movement}} + {{zh-l|*𭖒|knife}} + {{zh-l|*攵|to strike}} – originally meaning punishment.

Originally written as {{och-l|𭖒}} in oracle bone script; {{liushu|p|nocap=yes}} of a knife with tooth-shaped protrusions on the back. Variants which added {{och-l|*止|foot}} were common. In bronze inscriptions, {{och-l|*彳}} was often added to the character as well. In bamboo slips, {{och-l|*止}} was replaced with {{och-l|*攵}}, arriving at the modern form.

